1
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:34,100
Our Secret
EP08

2
00:01:35,550 --> 00:01:36,800
I see now.

3
00:01:37,310 --> 00:01:38,440
My daughter's grown up.

4
00:01:38,870 --> 00:01:40,950
You think you can make a choice by yourself, right?

5
00:01:41,270 --> 00:01:42,800
I can't control you anymore, right?

6
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,830
But I can still control you! Am I right?

7
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:50,000
I don't care!

8
00:01:51,310 --> 00:01:52,630
No matter what method you use,

9
00:01:52,830 --> 00:01:54,720
you have to change her to the liberal arts class!

10
00:01:55,590 --> 00:01:57,000
If you can't, let me tell you,

11
00:01:57,190 --> 00:01:57,830
from tomorrow,

12
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,120
wash your clothes yourself!

13
00:01:59,270 --> 00:02:00,040
Cook by yourself!

14
00:02:00,190 --> 00:02:01,440
I won't care about you anymore!

15
00:02:02,440 --> 00:02:03,270
You…

16
00:02:14,440 --> 00:02:15,440
Xianxian

17
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:18,390
Your teacher paid a home visit today.

18
00:02:18,829 --> 00:02:20,320
He gave us this.

19
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:24,320
That's what your mother's angry for.

20
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:27,030
Xianxian

21
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:29,520
Do you know why your mother's so angry?

22
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:31,670
She thinks you've grown up.

23
00:02:31,910 --> 00:02:33,190
and don't need her anymore.

24
00:02:33,390 --> 00:02:35,190
She doesn't know how to express it,

25
00:02:35,390 --> 00:02:36,750
so she behaves like that.

26
00:02:37,110 --> 00:02:38,630
You should understand her.

27
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:41,910
I should also criticize you.

28
00:02:42,190 --> 00:02:43,550
Why did you keep it as a secret

29
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,240
to hand in the application form?

30
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:50,190
Dad. It's my bad.

31
00:02:51,320 --> 00:02:53,160
I should have told you.

32
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:56,190
Please help me beg mom

33
00:02:56,470 --> 00:02:58,520
not to change me to the liberal arts class, okay?

34
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:01,270
I feel really happy at my present class.

35
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:05,470
And I don't want to be separated from my friends.

36
00:03:06,550 --> 00:03:09,030
Alright. As for your mom,

37
00:03:09,270 --> 00:03:10,800
I can help you.

38
00:03:11,470 --> 00:03:12,440
But,

39
00:03:12,910 --> 00:03:14,470
I am not that capable.

40
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:16,800
I can only give you one month.

41
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:18,000
For next monthly test,

42
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:19,520
try to get a good grade.

43
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:21,470
If you can do it,

44
00:03:22,110 --> 00:03:23,960
there will be a way out of this.

45
00:03:23,960 --> 00:03:24,670
Alight?

46
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:13,110
So students to the liberal arts and natural science classes

47
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:14,600
are temporarily settled.

48
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:17,269
It's not finalized, of course.

49
00:04:17,670 --> 00:04:20,000
If some of you still want to study liberal arts

50
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:22,230
after studying for a while in this class,

51
00:04:22,390 --> 00:04:23,790
tell me as soon as possible

52
00:04:23,950 --> 00:04:25,160
to change it.

53
00:04:26,390 --> 00:04:28,350
As for the placement test questions,

54
00:04:28,880 --> 00:04:29,880
I won't teach them.

55
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:32,760
Later I'll hand out answers to you.

56
00:04:33,070 --> 00:04:35,320
Analyze your errors after class,

57
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:37,670
and hand in the analysis before this Friday.

58
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:40,159
Alright. Let's continue.

59
00:04:46,110 --> 00:04:47,760
I can only give you one month.

60
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:48,950
For the next monthly test,

61
00:04:49,110 --> 00:04:50,550
try to get a good grade.

62
00:04:51,159 --> 00:04:52,480
If you can do it,

63
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:54,880
there will be a way out of this.

64
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:55,550
Alright?

65
00:05:04,110 --> 00:05:05,160
What's on your mind?

66
00:05:08,950 --> 00:05:09,920
I was thinking…

67
00:05:12,440 --> 00:05:13,760
I don't see great changes

68
00:05:13,950 --> 00:05:15,950
of this class placement.

69
00:05:16,440 --> 00:05:17,670
Because students who choose liberal arts

70
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:19,000
are few in reality.

71
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:21,160
No changes?

72
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,950
My dream girl, Yang Chunzi, left.

73
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:26,600
Now that you miss her so much,

74
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:29,760
just go with her.

75
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:32,510
It's too late.

76
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:36,760
Do you know anything else also late?

77
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:37,880
What?

78
00:05:39,510 --> 00:05:41,600
The game disc I lent to you before.

79
00:05:42,110 --> 00:05:43,040
I won't lend it now.

80
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:43,640
No, no, no.

81
00:05:43,950 --> 00:05:45,270
Please! Lend me for a while!

82
00:05:45,640 --> 00:05:47,000
Ask Yang Chunzi if she has it or not.

83
00:05:47,110 --> 00:05:48,110
Borrow it from her.

84
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:50,550
I won't give you.

85
00:05:50,550 --> 00:05:51,830
Song Ziqi! Kong Shadi!

86
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:53,550
Stand up!

87
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:57,720
It's all your fault.

88
00:06:00,790 --> 00:06:01,790
Stand back!

89
00:06:06,070 --> 00:06:08,200
Let's take out Mathematics Compulsory III.

90
00:06:09,350 --> 00:06:10,510
Turn to Page 23.

91
00:06:13,230 --> 00:06:14,640
Let's continue our class.

92
00:06:15,830 --> 00:06:18,350
Let's learn Euclidean algorithm.

93
00:06:19,510 --> 00:06:21,790
Euclidean algorithm is a kind of algorithm

94
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:23,950
recorded by Euclid in the "Elements".

95
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:26,920
Assume two integers are unequal.

96
00:06:27,110 --> 00:06:30,350
Divide the larger one by the smaller one.

97
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:31,320
If the remainder

98
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:33,600
is still a non-zero number,

99
00:06:33,790 --> 00:06:36,159
continue to divide until the remainder is zero.

100
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:44,510
Dad

101
00:06:45,390 --> 00:06:46,110
Xianxian

102
00:06:46,270 --> 00:06:47,720
Why do you come to this floor?

103
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:49,510
Didn't you say you would give me one month?

104
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:50,950
I come here to print a material.

105
00:06:51,159 --> 00:06:53,440
The printer upstairs breaks down. Don't worry.

106
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,390
Did you chat with my mom?

107
00:06:56,640 --> 00:06:57,950
Is she still angry?

108
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,230
Still a little bit.

109
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:03,480
She has another requirement for you.

110
00:07:03,790 --> 00:07:06,160
Get at least 270 points in natural science.

111
00:07:07,110 --> 00:07:08,880
That's killing me.

112
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:11,070
Just give my life to her!

113
00:07:11,350 --> 00:07:14,160
My silly girl! Your life was originally given by your mom.

114
00:07:15,350 --> 00:07:17,160
Well, I am not that capable.

115
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:18,830
That's all I can help you.

116
00:07:19,670 --> 00:07:20,760
Fighting!

117
00:07:22,390 --> 00:07:23,510
Thanks, Dad.

118
00:07:25,950 --> 00:07:28,110
How can I get 270 points?

119
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:36,720
Studying while preparing for the competition

120
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:39,110
is such a burden for normal people.

121
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:42,480
Poor thing!

122
00:07:54,230 --> 00:07:55,230
You are awake.

123
00:07:56,640 --> 00:07:58,670
Did you stay up late to study?

124
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:02,640
Aren't you too tired in this way?

125
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:04,390
Can you get enough sleep?

126
00:08:06,510 --> 00:08:07,600
It doesn't matter.

127
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:09,920
I've just made up for it.

128
00:08:19,510 --> 00:08:20,550
What happened to you?

129
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:25,160
May I ask you:

130
00:08:25,670 --> 00:08:26,640
Is there a way

131
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:28,230
to raise my grade to 270 points

132
00:08:28,270 --> 00:08:30,640
of natural science in one month?

133
00:08:37,150 --> 00:08:37,880
By dreaming.

134
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:44,440
Right now,

135
00:08:44,590 --> 00:08:45,760
don't think too much.

136
00:08:45,910 --> 00:08:47,080
Do more exam papers.

137
00:08:47,790 --> 00:08:50,200
At your current level, you cannot even get 250 points,

138
00:08:50,590 --> 00:08:51,790
let alone 270 points.

139
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:55,150
You're the 250 ("250" means "stupid" in Chinese)!

140
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:05,590
At least, I should work hard from now on.

141
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:06,910
Fighting!

142
00:09:26,470 --> 00:09:27,470
Come on, Congcong.

143
00:09:27,910 --> 00:09:28,960
Eat more meat.

144
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:31,400
Your body are growing. Eat more.

145
00:09:35,150 --> 00:09:36,000
Mom

146
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:39,000
Why did you make so many delicious dishes today?

147
00:09:39,350 --> 00:09:41,760
I wouldn't do it if you were not students.

148
00:09:43,150 --> 00:09:45,110
Come on. Dishes will be cold soon.

149
00:09:51,760 --> 00:09:52,710
Delicious!

150
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:01,710
Mom. Thanks for your hard work.

151
00:10:01,910 --> 00:10:02,840
Eat more.

152
00:10:04,960 --> 00:10:06,640
I've been cooking for over a decade.

153
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:08,590
Not until now have I heard a good word.

154
00:10:09,760 --> 00:10:10,880
Come on, Congcong.

155
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:12,550
Eat more.

156
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:18,670
What a big dinner this evening!

157
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:22,880
Where's mine?

158
00:10:30,910 --> 00:10:32,470
Well, I, I'm not that hungry.

159
00:10:33,350 --> 00:10:35,000
Help yourselves, help yourselves.

160
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:37,320
I'll go reading for a while.

161
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,230
Tomorrow is weekend.

162
00:11:02,030 --> 00:11:04,760
I'll take you to fill a prescription for your lenses.

163
00:11:06,230 --> 00:11:07,110
Thanks, Mom.

164
00:11:08,110 --> 00:11:09,230
Don't slack off in your study.

165
00:11:09,710 --> 00:11:12,000
Two hundred and seventy points. We've made a deal.

166
00:11:12,150 --> 00:11:13,470
One point less is not allowed.

167
00:11:19,110 --> 00:11:20,230
Two hundred and seventy.

168
00:11:20,520 --> 00:11:22,000
One point less is not allowed.

169
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:28,110
Be quiet.

170
00:11:28,550 --> 00:11:29,790
The last weekly physics test papers

171
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:30,790
have been handed out.

172
00:11:31,030 --> 00:11:32,320
Mr. Yang asks every student

173
00:11:32,470 --> 00:11:34,320
to bring the error analysis

174
00:11:34,350 --> 00:11:35,470
to him in his office in one week.

175
00:11:35,640 --> 00:11:36,590
Don't forget it.

176
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:02,110
What's going on?

177
00:12:02,760 --> 00:12:04,030
I'm helpless!

178
00:12:04,910 --> 00:12:05,910
Let me see.

179
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:17,910
You got the formula wrong for this question.

180
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,470
You should've got this score.

181
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:22,670
And this one.

182
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:25,400
You didn't understand this question well.

183
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:28,550
The mass of the ping-pong ball is a misleading proposition.

184
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:30,350
You should've also got this score.

185
00:12:34,910 --> 00:12:35,520
And this one.

186
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:37,640
It's even more unreasonable.

187
00:12:37,960 --> 00:12:39,320
Every procedure is right

188
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:41,520
except for the result, which is so easy to get.

189
00:12:42,110 --> 00:12:43,840
What were you thinking at that time?

190
00:12:45,110 --> 00:12:46,710
If I could do everything right,

191
00:12:47,150 --> 00:12:49,520
I would be the one to get 90 points.

192
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:52,110
No excuse for doing it wrongly.

193
00:12:55,550 --> 00:12:56,440
This one…

194
00:13:13,320 --> 00:13:14,230
Xianxian

195
00:13:15,590 --> 00:13:16,550
Su

196
00:13:17,350 --> 00:13:18,520
Why are you here?

197
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:21,550
Don't you need to take classes back in your university?

198
00:13:22,550 --> 00:13:23,640
The new term hasn't begun yet.

199
00:13:23,790 --> 00:13:25,150
So I want to come here to see you.

200
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:29,470
Are you free now?

201
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:45,150
Your mom is so demanding of you,

202
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:47,590
because she believes you are able to do it.

203
00:13:48,880 --> 00:13:50,350
Don't be discouraged.

204
00:13:51,150 --> 00:13:52,230
Because I also believe

205
00:13:52,760 --> 00:13:53,840
you can do it.

206
00:13:57,320 --> 00:13:59,200
I also thought I could,

207
00:14:00,110 --> 00:14:02,200
but no comparison, no harm.

208
00:14:05,470 --> 00:14:07,200
If there's anything you don't understand, you can ask me.

209
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:10,350
Didn't you learn liberal arts?

210
00:14:10,760 --> 00:14:11,910
You look down upon me, don't you?

211
00:14:12,110 --> 00:14:13,840
It's a piece of cake for me to teach you.

212
00:14:16,710 --> 00:14:18,320
Maybe I think

213
00:14:19,110 --> 00:14:21,230
I'm not that confident.

214
00:14:23,030 --> 00:14:24,280
Thanks anyway, Su.

215
00:14:25,350 --> 00:14:25,910
Oh, right.

216
00:14:26,670 --> 00:14:28,150
I have another thing to say.

217
00:14:30,550 --> 00:14:31,670
On the day of the graduation ceremony,

218
00:14:31,760 --> 00:14:33,080
I wanted to take a photo with you.

219
00:14:33,590 --> 00:14:34,640
But I didn't get a chance.

220
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:36,110
You should make it up to me today.

221
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:37,790
No problem.

222
00:14:38,790 --> 00:14:39,400
Come here.

223
00:14:56,910 --> 00:14:58,150
How time flies!

224
00:14:58,350 --> 00:14:59,760
You're a college student now.

225
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:02,840
Does it mean we won't see each other for a long time?

226
00:15:04,080 --> 00:15:04,760
What are you afraid of?

227
00:15:04,910 --> 00:15:06,200
I'll come back during vacation.

228
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:11,520
I should go back for the class.

229
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:13,710
Our class supervisor will come there soon.

230
00:15:19,590 --> 00:15:20,320
Xianxian

231
00:15:36,350 --> 00:15:37,230
This is for you.

232
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:43,080
I hope you

233
00:15:44,470 --> 00:15:46,000
can smile like that forever.

234
00:15:49,350 --> 00:15:50,110
Definitely.

235
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:53,960
Go back for your class.

236
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:17,590
Xianxian, it just occurred to me…

237
00:16:21,790 --> 00:16:23,520
Who took this photo for you?

238
00:16:23,790 --> 00:16:25,400
Su took it for me just now.

239
00:16:25,470 --> 00:16:26,280
Let me see. Let me see.

240
00:16:26,350 --> 00:16:27,710
Look at the smile while looking back.

241
00:16:28,760 --> 00:16:30,150
Su really knows how to take photos!

242
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:31,790
Look, look, look.

243
00:16:33,840 --> 00:16:35,760
I've written down reasons why you made mistakes.

244
00:16:35,910 --> 00:16:37,280
Look at them carefully this evening.

245
00:16:38,350 --> 00:16:39,670
And there are two papers.

246
00:16:41,350 --> 00:16:42,960
Finish them and give me tomorrow.

247
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:48,230
Two papers for one evening?

248
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:50,640
If you find them hard, don't do them.

249
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:53,110
If you get 200 points, you can still go to a college.

250
00:16:54,910 --> 00:16:56,230
I didn't mean it.

251
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:58,110
Zhou Siyue

252
00:16:58,520 --> 00:17:00,670
Why are you so cruel to our Xianxian?

253
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:03,400
Am I cruel to her?

254
00:17:03,910 --> 00:17:05,710
College entrance examination is much crueler than me.

255
00:17:05,950 --> 00:17:07,280
I'm helping her.

256
00:17:11,160 --> 00:17:12,000
How about that?

257
00:17:12,560 --> 00:17:14,880
Pay attention to the National Mathematics Olympiad first.

258
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:20,680
Fine. I won't care about you anymore.

259
00:17:46,310 --> 00:17:47,350
Xianxian

260
00:17:48,950 --> 00:17:50,560
Why haven't you been to the school?

261
00:17:51,040 --> 00:17:53,350
Good morning. I'm waiting for Zhou Siyue.

262
00:17:53,520 --> 00:17:54,640
Did he go downstairs?

263
00:17:55,560 --> 00:17:56,830
Didn't he tell you?

264
00:17:57,190 --> 00:17:59,310
He went to the training camp with other team members

265
00:17:59,350 --> 00:18:01,230
of the Olympiad by bus this early morning.

266
00:18:05,310 --> 00:18:06,350
I see.

267
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:08,280
I'll go to school now, Madam.

268
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:10,310
Be careful.

269
00:18:11,040 --> 00:18:11,830
Good-bye, Madam.

270
00:18:11,830 --> 00:18:12,470
Good-bye.

271
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:20,230
With huge waves are gone all those. Gallant heroes of bygone years.
(A Song Poem by Su Shi)

272
00:18:20,590 --> 00:18:22,000
West of the ancient fortress appears.

273
00:18:22,310 --> 00:18:26,110
At Red Cliff General Zhou won fame during the Three Kingdom.

274
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:29,760
Rocks tower in the air and waves teat on the shore.

275
00:18:30,110 --> 00:18:32,160
Rolling up a thousand heaps of snow.

276
00:18:37,640 --> 00:18:39,640
Zhou Siyue is off for the National Olympiad.

277
00:18:41,470 --> 00:18:42,640
Not until now do I notice

278
00:18:43,230 --> 00:18:44,400
that it's so hard to get used to the days

279
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:45,640
without a deskmate.

280
00:18:48,190 --> 00:18:49,760
It seems as if he went to

281
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:51,310
a battlefield alone.

282
00:18:52,760 --> 00:18:54,680
It may just be my illusion.

283
00:18:56,310 --> 00:18:57,230
After all,

284
00:18:58,310 --> 00:18:59,470
he should be very familiar with

285
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:01,310
this kind of competition life.

286
00:19:11,560 --> 00:19:13,710
